It's been a while since I've seen that smile but the old magic's still there.  And I love what you've done with your hair...  We may not get back what we had, what I threw away, but you know I would do anything, anything you say. I'd cross a thousand miles of broken glass on my hands and knees, I would crawl if for a moment we could cease hostilities.  I don't know where I am, I don't know where I went wrong, but it seemed like such a good idea at the time, such a very very good idea at the time.  Now our dream is over, but lately I have found that you only seem to come alive when I am not around. 
  
     But is it just me or am I all on my own again? You're at the Taj Mahal, I'm outside Big Ben,
it's driving me round the bend. I see your face when I close my eyes, don't want a life alone
all by myself. I wanna give you my love, my love, my love. 

     We had a good thing, it was a blast, that was a long time in the past. You went through changes & I went away, and I have regretted that to this day.  I may not always have quite so much hair but what you saw in me will hopefully always be there. I'll never hurt you again, I swear. Forgive and forget I caused you some pain, find it in your heart to start again.  Now I may not ever be your Mister Right, but I'm happy to be your mister that will do for tonight.


      Girl, I know I've got a funny way of showing it, yes, I thought our love was here to stay, and blowing it was never on my agenda. Girl I know I ripped your heart right out so why pretend that there is even a shadow of doubt that it's the end. Why the hell are we breaking our necks?

       I fell for you and you grew to like me, we rolled around, kissing on the ground. You succumbed to my charms, fell asleep in my arms, beneath the stars above we fell in love. YOU'RE a bonefide fucking genius, frolicking in the autumn fields were we. I cherished you and you tolerated me.

So I've been playing slide guitar, and delta blues.  A lot has happened that I don't want to go into. So this morning I was at the gas station and I was distracted by something and I forgot to put the cap back on the tank.  I got to school saw it was missing and I was like "Fuck".  I decided to go back to the gas station after school and I asked the clerk if anyone had turned in a cap but he said no, it turns out it was over in some grass by a tree. I don't know what I believe but I do am sure of one thing, Karma.  I do good deeds and I'm repaid, sure like when I find money and I turn it in ppl call me stupid, I don't like having guilt. I need to get a band going,  when we are ready we'll make a demo, I'll give it to Marv, he'll give it to his manager and the record label he is on,  we will hopefully get a manager and signed, and then we will rock, and make lots of money.  The problem is finding the band members, they need to be good and reliable.  Like not getting arrested and being grounded for 2 months would be ideal.  LATER.

When love comes so late, it'll really hit hard

But after awhile I stopped to rebel 
I'm back in the past and I'm raising up hell 

But I think I've just made the biggest mistake of my life 
And I think I've just made the biggest mistake of my life 

We'd been living together for over a year 
The harmony's perfect, it rang loud and clear 
But then very slowly, my nerves start to fray 
The little things big, that's what they say 

I acted impatient, I acted unkind 
I took her for granted, I played with her mind

I walked out the door and left her to her fate 

But I think I've just made the biggest mistake of my life
